Each unsuffixed file has a paired `-basic.bd` teaching version.

Each public route imports both levels.

These files are written in the intended final shape. They do not supersede
`docs/language-overview.md` until the complete language migration and parity
review have been approved.

## Public documentation

`docs/src/docs/**` contains website pages, teaching references, examples and
topic navigation.

## Design boundaries

`docs/src/docs/codebase/design-scope/overview.bd` summarises accepted
mechanisms, constraints and intentionally excluded complexity.

## Memory access

`docs/src/docs/codebase/memory-management/access-and-aliasing/overview.bd`
covers shared reads, explicit copies and `~` access.

## Compiler ownership

`docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/overview.bd` routes language features
to the compiler stages and subsystems that implement them.
